sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_rounds_played
FROM rounds
WHERE course_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(hole_id) AS total_holes_played
FROM holes
WHERE course_id = (SELECT course_id FROM courses WHERE course_name = 'Pebble Beach Golf Links');

external_knowledge:
- Pebble Beach Golf Links is a famous golf course; 
- A round in golf typically consists of 18 holes; 
- Playing more than 10 rounds implies that a golfer has significant experience at the course.

sql:
SELECT MIN(par) AS best_par
FROM holes
WHERE hole_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
The Masters Tournament is one of the major golf tournaments, held annually at Augusta National Golf Club; 
Birdie refers to a score of one stroke under the par of a hole; 
Par is the predetermined number of strokes a skilled golfer should take to complete a hole or a round.
